<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><rss xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom" version="2.0"><channel><title>World News, Today World News, Latest International News, World Breaking News, Trending News of World - Times of India</title><link>https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world</link><description>World News Today: Read the latest world news headlines, Current International breaking news world wide. In depth analysis and top news headlines world wide.</description><language>en-gb</language><lastBuildDate>2026-07-11T00:21:44+05:30</lastBuildDate><atom:link type="application/rss+xml" rel="self" href="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/rssfeeds/296589292.cms"/><copyright>Copyright:(C) Sat, 11 Jul 2026 00:21:44 IST Bennett Coleman &amp; Co. Ltd, http://in.indiatimes.com/policyterms/1554651.cms</copyright><docs>http://syndication.indiatimes.com/</docs><image><title>World News, Today World News, Latest International News, World Breaking News, Trending News of World - Times of India</title><url>https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/507610.cms</url><link>https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world</link></image><item><title><![CDATA[Pak refuses to accept grooming gang leader unless UK hands over political dissidents]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132318854.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[Pakistan demands UK extradition of dissidents for deporting Shabir Ahmed.  Ahmed, a grooming gang leader, faces deportation after his British citizenship was revoked.  Pakistan states it will not accept him without reciprocal extradition agreements.  Islamabad wants UK extradition of figures like Shahzad Akbar and Adil Raja.  This creates a stalemate, with the UK unlikely to extradite dissidents.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/uk/pak-refuses-to-accept-grooming-gang-leader-unless-uk-hands-over-political-dissidents/articleshow/132318854.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/uk/pak-refuses-to-accept-grooming-gang-leader-unless-uk-hands-over-political-dissidents/articleshow/132318854.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-11T00:13:20+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">Naomi Canton</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132318833,imgsize-40860.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[No, I am in Dublin: PwC worker remotely works from India; lies when confronted, accuses boss of bullying]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132319247.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/europe/no-i-am-in-dublin-pwc-worker-remotely-works-from-india-lies-when-confronted-accuses-boss-of-bullying/articleshow/132319247.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/europe/no-i-am-in-dublin-pwc-worker-remotely-works-from-india-lies-when-confronted-accuses-boss-of-bullying/articleshow/132319247.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-11T00:04:05+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132319332,imgsize-136506.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Mark Zuckerberg wore a $2 million vintage watch from the 1950s that tracks the cycles of the moon]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132317687.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[Mark Zuckerberg, adorned with a vintage Rolex Stelline, articulates the pivotal role of AI in transforming medical research. His Biohub initiative emphasizes combating human illnesses through sophisticated computer models. The Stelline, a rare and coveted collector's watch, is valued in the millions, reflecting Zuckerberg's refined taste in luxury timepieces, paralleling his push for technological progress in health.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/technology/tech-news/meta-ceo-mark-zuckerberg-wore-a-2-million-vintage-watch-from-the-1950s-that-tracks-the-cycles-of-the-moon-while-talking-about-how-ai-could-help-medical-research/articleshow/132317687.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/technology/tech-news/meta-ceo-mark-zuckerberg-wore-a-2-million-vintage-watch-from-the-1950s-that-tracks-the-cycles-of-the-moon-while-talking-about-how-ai-could-help-medical-research/articleshow/132317687.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-10T23:17:52+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132317877,imgsize-109566.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Scientists have debunked the long-repeated myth that baby rattlesnakes are more dangerous than adults, finding that adult rattlesnakes usually deliver more venom and cause more serious bites]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132308493.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[A new study challenges the long-held belief that baby rattlesnakes are more dangerous. Researchers found young snakes can control venom expulsion, similar to adults. Adult rattlesnakes carry and inject significantly more venom, causing more severe symptoms. This misconception has led to negative consequences and unwarranted fear among people. The study traced the myth's spread through media reports over decades.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/science/scientists-have-debunked-the-long-repeated-myth-that-baby-rattlesnakes-are-more-dangerous-than-adults-finding-that-adult-rattlesnakes-usually-deliver-more-venom-and-cause-more-serious-bites/articleshow/132308493.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/science/scientists-have-debunked-the-long-repeated-myth-that-baby-rattlesnakes-are-more-dangerous-than-adults-finding-that-adult-rattlesnakes-usually-deliver-more-venom-and-cause-more-serious-bites/articleshow/132308493.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-10T21:12:50+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI Science Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132309747,imgsize-271406.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[A pizza oven window shattered in 37 reported incidents, Cuisinart is recalling the entire grill]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132310578.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[Conair has recalled the Cuisinart Propel+ Four Burner 3-in-1 Gas Grill due to a shattering glass window.  Thirty-seven incidents of glass shattering were reported in the United States.  One fire incident was also reported, posing a laceration risk to consumers.  Customers must remove the glass and upload photos to receive a refund.  The grill was sold at Lowes and Walmart from December 2024 to May 2026.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/rest-of-world/a-pizza-oven-window-shattered-in-37-reported-incidents-cuisinart-is-recalling-the-entire-grill/articleshow/132310578.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/rest-of-world/a-pizza-oven-window-shattered-in-37-reported-incidents-cuisinart-is-recalling-the-entire-grill/articleshow/132310578.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-10T20:33:53+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132310882,imgsize-919876.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Pakistan launches crackdown after Balochistan attacks, claims 75 BLA militants killed]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132317732.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[In a series of military operations in Balochistan province, Pakistan security forces took decisive action, leading to the death of seventy-five militants. This response came in the wake of fatal attacks on police and civilians blamed on the BLA. An earlier clash near Mangi Dam saw nine policemen and fifteen attackers dead. Prime Minister Sharif's visit to Quetta promised justice and financial compensation for the bereaved families.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/pakistan/pakistan-launches-crackdown-after-balochistan-attacks-claims-75-bla-militants-killed/articleshow/132317732.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/pakistan/pakistan-launches-crackdown-after-balochistan-attacks-claims-75-bla-militants-killed/articleshow/132317732.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-10T23:05:50+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI News Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132317746,imgsize-49868.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Green Card of Kuwaiti artist revoked for calling America 'enemy']]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132317215.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/green-card-of-kuwaiti-artist-revoked-for-calling-america-enemy-foreign-nationals-who-echo-propaganda-should-find-themselves-on-deportation-flight/articleshow/132317215.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/green-card-of-kuwaiti-artist-revoked-for-calling-america-enemy-foreign-nationals-who-echo-propaganda-should-find-themselves-on-deportation-flight/articleshow/132317215.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-10T22:51:19+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132317368,imgsize-81550.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[5 things you probably didn’t know about Erling Haaland, the Viking striker who helped Norway make FIFA World Cup history]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132315752.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[Erling Haaland is making headlines as he propels Norway to an unforgettable World Cup quarter-final by scoring seven goals. Born in England but raised in Norway, his unique background sparks conversations. Haaland, an advocate for social justice, has a notable online presence. Football runs in his blood, as his father was a pro player, and he famously dabbled in rap.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/sports/football/fifa-world-cup/5-things-you-probably-didnt-know-about-erling-haaland-the-viking-striker-who-helped-norway-make-fifa-world-cup-history/articleshow/132315752.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/sports/football/fifa-world-cup/5-things-you-probably-didnt-know-about-erling-haaland-the-viking-striker-who-helped-norway-make-fifa-world-cup-history/articleshow/132315752.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-10T22:36:26+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132316986,imgsize-246062.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Quote of the day by Will Smith: "If you're not making someone else's life better, then you're wasting your time."]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132315948.cms" /&gt;<![CDAT